article.headline: Rebounds key in No. 24 Florida State's victory
article.linkText: Rebounds key in No. 24 Florida State's victory
article.story:
TALLAHASSEE, Fla. --  Tanae Davis-Cain and Jacinta Monroe combined for 33 points, including 21 in the second half, as  Florida State (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) turned back a furious Florida Gulf Coast rally for an 81-62 season-opening victory.

The Seminoles used a commanding 45-23 rebounding advantage to hold off the Eagles, who opened the season with an 88-86 upset victory of Florida.

Davis-Cain led five double-figure scorers with a game-high 18 points, including consecutive 3-pointers in the second half after Florida Gulf Coast whittled a 22-point deficit to 45-39 with 13:09 to play. Monroe contributed 15 points and 12 rebounds and started a 12-2 Seminoles run with a layup.

Florida Gulf Coast (1-1) never completely recovered after missing 11 of its first 12 shots. Kelsey Jacobson, who led the Eagles with 14 points, knocked down a trio of 3-pointers during the rally.
